PN,44302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1779307555
OL,3,CBelfast Harbour to invest #1.3bn over
OL,4,Cnext 25 years
OL,6,FThe #1.3 billion will "ensure that the
OL,7,Fport remains resilient, efficient and
OL,8,Fcompetitive, capable of supporting
OL,9,Feconomic growth across Northern
OL,10,FIreland and the wider island for
OL,11,Fdecades to come".
OL,13,FThe 2025-2050 Masterplan sets out how
OL,14,Fthe port will provide planned,
OL,15,Fsustainable capacity to support trade
OL,16,Fflows and strengthen supply chains.
OL,18,FBelfast Harbour handles 70% of
OL,19,FNorthern Ireland's seaborne trade and
OL,20,Fa quarter of all seaborne trade of the
OL,21,Fentire island of Ireland.
OL,26,@nD@WOUsD@PO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1779307555
OL,3,CBelfast Harbour to invest #1.3bn over
OL,4,Cnext 25 years
OL,6,FIt is the second busiest port on the
OL,7,Fisland and one of the UK's top 10,
OL,8,Fsupporting more than 760 businesses
OL,9,Fand around 20,000 jobs.
OL,11,FForecasts indicate trade volumes
OL,12,Fthrough Belfast Harbour could increase
OL,13,Ffrom around 24 million tonnes today to
OL,14,Fmore than 30 million tonnes by 2050
OL,15,Funder steady growth, and to between 40
OL,16,Fmillion and 50 million tonnes under
OL,17,Fhighergrowth scenarios.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1779307555
OL,3,CBelfast Harbour to invest #1.3bn over
OL,4,Cnext 25 years
OL,6,FThe first phase from 2025-2029
OL,7,Fincludes the development of a new #90
OL,8,Fmillion dual purpose deepwater cruise
OL,9,Fand wind energy terminal.
OL,11,FProposed projects in the second phase
OL,12,F2030-2040 include the redevelopment of
OL,13,FStormont Wharf, a vital quay that
OL,14,Falready supports a range of mixed
OL,15,Fcargo uses and the expansion of
OL,16,FBelfast Harbour Marina to boost
OL,17,Fleisure and tourism growth.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G4/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNI NewsCClean Feed FThis Day
FL,444,440,140,120,000,100
PN,44305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F443A1779307555
OL,3,CBelfast Harbour to invest #1.3bn over
OL,4,Cnext 25 years
OL,6,FThe 2040-2050 phase of the scheme
OL,7,Fproposes a new terminal for freight
OL,8,Ftransported by container or trailer at
OL,9,Fthe end of the West Bank Road `
OL,10,FBelfast Harbour's first land
OL,11,Freclamation project for 25 years ` as
OL,12,Fwell as establishing a Clean Energy
OL,13,FHub to provide for new fuels and
OL,14,Fencourage a reduction in hydrocarbon
OL,15,Fland use.
OL,17,FInfrastructure minister Liz Kimmins
OL,18,Fsaid the 2025-2050 Masterplan
OL,19,F"captures a bold and exciting future
OL,20,Ffor Belfast Harbour".
OL,26,@{D@AOU|D@TO]
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/12
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
